ResourceHeader.ResourceName: Voyager 2 Uranus CRS Resampled Summary D2 Rate Electron 96-s V1.0
ResourceHeader.Description:
Counting rate from the D2 detector in the Cosmic Ray                          
System (CRS) electron telescope (TET) on Voyager 2 during                     
the Uranus encounter.                                                         
The D2 detector nominally responds to electrons with                          
kinetic energies above approximately 2.5 MeV                                  
(see detector description for details).                                       
                                                                              
    SAMPLING_PARAMETER_NAME         = TIME                                    
    SAMPLING_PARAMETER_RESOLUTION   = 6.0                                     
    MINIMUM_SAMPLING_PARAMETER      = N/A                                     
    MAXIMUM_SAMPLING_PARAMETER      = N/A                                     
    SAMPLING_PARAMETER_INTERVAL     = 96.0                                    
    MINIMUM_AVAILABLE_SAMPLING_INT  = 96.0                                    
    SAMPLING_PARAMETER_UNIT         = SECOND                                  
    DATA_SET_PARAMETER_NAME         = D2 RATE                                 
    NOISE_LEVEL                     = 0.000                                   
    DATA_SET_PARAMETER_UNIT         = COUNTS/SECOND
